&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Description:&lt;/strong&gt; Systemiq is the system change company, working to accelerate the transition to a net-zero, nature-positive and more inclusive economy. As a certified B Corp, we partner with business, finance, policymakers and civil society to transform five interconnected systems: energy, nature and food, materials and circularity, sustainable finance, and urban transformation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;2454&quot; data-end=&quot;2786&quot;&gt;We bring together strategy, policy, market design and capital mobilisation to deliver tangible results in the real economy. Founded in 2016, Systemiq has grown to a global team of more than 300 people across Brazil, France, Germany, Indonesia, Kenya, the Netherlands, the UK and the US, united by a singular focus on sustainability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Associate Manager, Nature &amp;amp; Food&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Nairobi, Kenya&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an Associate Manager to help deliver high-impact projects across SYSTEMIQ&#39;s Nature &amp;amp; Food platform in Kenya and the wider East African region.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working with governments, businesses, financial institutions, development partners and civil society, you will tackle complex challenges at the intersection of sustainable development, economic growth and systems transformation. Depending on project priorities, your work may span sustainable finance, labour markets, workforce development, skills systems, food systems and nature-positive growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is suited to an experienced consultant who combines structured problem-solving with strong stakeholder management and project leadership. You will lead significant workstreams, manage senior relationships, coach junior colleagues and help translate analysis into practical recommendations that create real-world impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Delivery&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead complex project workstreams from problem definition through to delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Structure analyses, develop insights and deliver high-quality outputs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate evidence into practical recommendations for clients and partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to project planning, quality assurance and delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder Engagement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build trusted relationships with clients and partners across government, finance, business, NGOs and development organisations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate workshops and multi-stakeholder discussions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help align diverse stakeholders around shared objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team &amp;amp; Platform Contribution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coach Associates and Senior Associates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to proposals, business development and thought leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster a collaborative, entrepreneurial team culture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use AI tools responsibly to enhance research, analysis and communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Candidate Profile&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an intellectually curious, impact-driven consultant who enjoys solving complex problems and working across disciplines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be comfortable leading workstreams, managing senior stakeholders and delivering high-quality analysis in fast-paced, multi-stakeholder environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Description:&lt;/strong&gt; Systemiq is the system change company, working to accelerate the transition to a net-zero, nature-positive and more inclusive economy. As a certified B Corp, we partner with business, finance, policymakers and civil society to transform five interconnected systems: energy, nature and food, materials and circularity, sustainable finance, and urban transformation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;2454&quot; data-end=&quot;2786&quot;&gt;We bring together strategy, policy, market design and capital mobilisation to deliver tangible results in the real economy. Founded in 2016, Systemiq has grown to a global team of more than 300 people across Brazil, France, Germany, Indonesia, Kenya, the Netherlands, the UK and the US, united by a singular focus on sustainability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;London Option&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;967&quot; data-end=&quot;1287&quot;&gt;As a Strategy Associate, you will play a key role in delivering high-impact advisory work within the Materials and Circular Economy platform. This is a client-facing role requiring strong structured problem-solving, analytical thinking, and the ability to translate complex topics into clear, actionable recommendations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1289&quot; data-end=&quot;1569&quot;&gt;You will work as part of small, fast-paced project teams supporting corporate and public sector clients on strategic questions related to circularity and sustainability. This includes framing problems, analysing data, developing insights, and contributing to client-ready outputs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1571&quot; data-end=&quot;1814&quot;&gt;We are looking for someone who either brings experience from a strategy consulting or advisory environment, or who can quickly operate at that level—demonstrating strong analytical rigour, clear communication, and comfort working in ambiguity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul data-start=&quot;1880&quot; data-end=&quot;2475&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1880&quot; data-end=&quot;1962&quot; data-section-id=&quot;oyjusf&quot;&gt;Structure complex, ambiguous problems into clear workstreams and key questions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1963&quot; data-end=&quot;2042&quot; data-section-id=&quot;pck17y&quot;&gt;Conduct rigorous qualitative and quantitative analysis to generate insights&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;2043&quot; data-end=&quot;2141&quot; data-section-id=&quot;g8czom&quot;&gt;Translate analysis into clear, concise, and compelling recommendations (often in slide format)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;2142&quot; data-end=&quot;2210&quot; data-section-id=&quot;1lzmggf&quot;&gt;Support the development of client deliverables and presentations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;2211&quot; data-end=&quot;2298&quot; data-section-id=&quot;1qqjfai&quot;&gt;Work directly with clients and partners across private sector, government, and NGOs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;2299&quot; data-end=&quot;2380&quot; data-section-id=&quot;1nai5sj&quot;&gt;Contribute to shaping project approaches, hypotheses, and strategic direction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;2381&quot; data-end=&quot;2475&quot; data-section-id=&quot;1sut1yd&quot;&gt;Build strong, trust-based relationships with stakeholders across multi-partner initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;: You will be part of the Materials &amp;amp; Circular Economy team, led by Partner Ben Dixon. Ben works across the circular economy and energy platforms and has collaborated with clients like the Ellen MacArthur Foundation, the United Nations International Resource Panel, and large multinational companies in the packaging and chemicals industries. He also manages

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Description:&lt;/strong&gt; Systemiq is the system change company, working to accelerate the transition to a net-zero, nature-positive and more inclusive economy. As a certified B Corp, we partner with business, finance, policymakers and civil society to transform five interconnected systems: energy, nature and food, materials and circularity, sustainable finance, and urban transformation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;2454&quot; data-end=&quot;2786&quot;&gt;We bring together strategy, policy, market design and capital mobilisation to deliver tangible results in the real economy. Founded in 2016, Systemiq has grown to a global team of more than 300 people across Brazil, France, Germany, Indonesia, Kenya, the Netherlands, the UK and the US, united by a singular focus on sustainability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Director, Power Systems &amp;amp; Grid Transformation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Amsterdam ( preferred), or London &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports to:&lt;/strong&gt; Eveline Speelman, Global Energy Platform Lead&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Systemiq is seeking a Director with deep expertise in power system transformation, with a particular focus on grids, system planning, flexibility, market design, utility transformation, and the integration of renewables at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will help clients address some of the most critical bottlenecks in the energy transition: grid constraints, connection queues, system adequacy, flexibility markets, transmission and distribution investment, regulatory reform, and the changing role of utilities and system operators.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not a generalist energy transition role. We are looking for a senior strategy leader who understands how power systems actually work technically, commercially, and institutionally, and who can help clients unlock the grid, market, and system integration challenges now slowing the transition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a senior leadership role combining:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep power systems expertise&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Top-tier strategy problem solving&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Origination and senior client leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delivery of complex, multi-stakeholder programmes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team leadership and platform-building&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work closely with Eveline Speelman and global partners to build Systemiq’s work on power system transformation, with a particular focus on grids, flexibility, market design, utilities, and system-level decarbonisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Power Systems &amp;amp; Grid Transformation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead work on power system transformation, including grid constraints, transmission and distribution investment, system planning, flexibility, renewables integration, and utility transformation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise clients on the strategic, regulatory, commercial, and institutional choices needed to accelerate power system decarbonisation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate technical power system challenges into clear strategic recommendations for senior decision-makers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify the practical barriers slowing power system transformation and shape interventions to overcome them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Advisory&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead high-impact strategy engagements with corporates, governments, investors, utilities, system operators, and other energy system actors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Structure and solve complex, ambiguous problems and translate them into actionable recommendations.

